<section id="problem">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>The Problem</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        U.S. bridges, buildings, and public infrastructure fail primarily due to
        <strong>localized stress concentrations</strong> that initiate cracks long before visible damage occurs.
        Inspection and repair methods are reactive, labor-intensive, and increasingly unsustainable under
        climate-driven loading and workforce shortages.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="solution">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Our Solution</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        InfraHeal develops <strong>stress-selective, self-healing composite materials</strong> that autonomously respond
        only where failure risk is highest. By embedding decision-making capability directly into materials,
        we extend service life and reduce maintenance costs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="technology">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Core Technology</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Shape Memory Polymer (SMP) matrices</strong> for controlled crack closure</li>
        <li><strong>Fiber-reinforced composites</strong> for stress localization (strain/resistance response)</li>
        <li><strong>Localized activation</strong> (thermal or magnetic) confined to critical regions</li>
        <li><strong>Decision-support analytics</strong> using Python-based visualization</li>
      </ul>

      <div style="margin-top:10px;">
        <span class="tag">Self-Healing</span>
        <span class="tag">Stress-Selective</span>
        <span class="tag">Infrastructure</span>
        <span class="tag">Smart Materials</span>
      </div>

      <!-- OPTIONAL: add more images later by putting files in /images and referencing them here -->
