<section id="research">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Research Foundation</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        InfraHeal’s platform is grounded in experimentally validated research, including peer-reviewed publications
        on self-healing composites, shape-memory polymers, and multifunctional material systems.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Self-Healing of Macroscopic Cracks in Concrete by Cellulose Fiber-Carried Microbes (2024)</li>
        <li>Efficacy of Cellulose Fiber as Bacteria Carrier for Self-Healing Concrete</li>
        <li>Development of Multifunctional Wood Composites with Integrated Phase Change Materials</li>
        <li>Effect of Two-Way Shape Memory on Healing of Polymer Composites</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top:14px; color:var(--muted);">
        These works inform the material design principles underlying InfraHeal’s stress-selective self-healing platform.
        No intellectual property conflicts exist.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="team">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Leadership & Expertise</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        <strong>Emmanuel Igbokwe, M.Sc., M.Eng.</strong><br />
        Founder & CEO | Principal Investigator
      </p>
      <p>
        Materials and infrastructure engineer with expertise in self-healing composites, shape-memory polymers,
        advanced materials characterization (DMA, DSC, TGA, SEM, MTS), and applied data analytics.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top:18px;">
        <strong>Machine Learning & Neural Systems (Advisory)</strong><br />
        Applied to stress, strain, and damage evolution data for predictive maintenance and future adaptive material behavior.
        Machine learning methods are applied at the <strong>decision-support layer</strong>, complementing the core materials innovation.
      </p>
    </div>
